content:
A man is said to have committed rape when he has had intercourse with a woman under any of the following situations:
1. Against her will; without her consent; 
2. With her consent:
a. But when her consent has been obtained by threatening to cause harm to her or to the people she cares about;
b. When the man knows that he is not her husband; 
c. When she doesn't understand the consequences;
3. With or without her consent, when she is under 16.
